ught, Pivotal Politics remakes our understanding of American lawmaking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLawxPolitical aspects. 0aLegislationzUnited States. 0aSeparation of powerszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  apolitics, political science, legislation, lawmaking, congress, courts, government, partisanship, productivity, gridlock, compromise, across the aisle, bipartisanship, bill, vote, filibuster, veto, coalition, supermajority, presidential power, executive, legislative, branches, separation of powers, checks and balances, nonfiction.1 aKrehbiel, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226452739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226452739/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles